Steps for backend:
    a. Initialize a Node.js project in the `backend` directory.
    b. Install required packages: express, mongoose, jsonwebtoken, socket.io, twilio (or other SMS provider), dotenv, etc.
    c. Set up a basic Express server.
    d. Connect to MongoDB (we can use MongoDB Atlas for cloud database).
    e. Define User and Message models.
    f. Implement routes for:
        - Sending OTP
        - Verifying OTP and registering/logging in
        - Fetching user profile
        - Sending a message (via HTTP and then via Socket.IO for real-time)
        - Fetching message history for a chat
    g. Set up Socket.IO to broadcast messages to the intended recipient.
